Reasoning: The paper analyzes the behavior and preferences of users on Sina Weibo, a Chinese micro-blogging service, and compares it with Twitter. The analysis includes studying the degree distribution, assortative mixing, friend similarities, following distribution, and message forwarding behavior. This work involves social network analysis, natural language processing, and multimedia analysis, which are relevant to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
